1. Moj brat će se uskoro *oženiti*. (My brother will soon get *married*.)
2. Njegova želja je da se *oženi* bogatom naslednicom. (His desire is to *marry* a wealthy heiress.)
3. Kada se *ožene*, živeće u kući koju su zajedno kupili. (When they *get married*, they will live in a house they bought together.)
4. Njegova majka stalno ga nagovara da se *oženi*. (His mother keeps pushing him to *get married*.)
5. Njegova baka mu je ostavila novac da se *oženi* pre nego što umre. (His grandmother left him money to *get married* before she dies.)
6. On je srećno *oženjen* već 10 godina. (He has been happily *married* for 10 years.)
7. Većina muškaraca se *oženi* iz ljubavi, ali neki iz interesa. (Most men *get married* out of love, but some for interest.)
8. On planira da se *oženi* sledeće godine. (He plans to *get married* next year.)
9. Oni su *oženjeni* u crkvi, ali nisu imali građansko venčanje. (They got *married* in church, but they didn't have a civil wedding.)
10. Moj deda se *oženio* kada je imao samo 20 godina. (My grandfather *got married* when he was only 20 years old.)